long_desc.thetext: Gee. This restarts the war with jikes parser generator. Sigh.

(In reply to comment #1) > Gee. This restarts the war with jikes parser generator. Sigh.
I have one big hammer (i.e the VanguardParser) and every problem looks like a nail (i.e a look ahead problem). By manufacturing and injecting synthetic tokens, I am able to pound the grammar into LALR(1). Anybody is welcome to take a look at alternate more traditional solutions.

(In reply to comment #2)
> Anybody is welcome to take a look at alternate more traditional solutions.
The way the language parsing challenges are growing, look ahead is fast becoming the traditional solution ! I shudder to think of Java 9, 10, 11 ...
